> Probably you get hit by this?
>
> https://github.com/apache/httpd/blob/46a9db4c6f9fadca4e362872021fa62a37908ece/server/mpm/event/event.c#L2096-L2101

With PR #294 this specific case shouldn't happen anymore (thanks to
https://github.com/apache/httpd/pull/294/commits/7089813e13bba0f25bd34df4c643cf5878e6e043).
Also, every connection killed by the MPM (timeout, internal error..)
should have an mpm_event:info message (AH10380), do you see any in
your logs Graham?

What might happen still is that a kept-alive connection gets closed by
httpd, after KeepAliveTimeout usually but also as soon as httpd gets
short in worker threads
(https://github.com/apache/httpd/blob/trunk/server/mpm/event/event.c#L2260-L2262),
and in both cases I'm not sure ab wouldn't report the same error
anyway..

